Hey,

this is my second map. This time i worked togheter with Chuck Norris.
The Map has 8 Stages, 6 Jails (5 after finishing the map, 1 after timeleft.), 
and 1 littl bonus in every Stage. Both of us worked on the Stages so every Stage has something of me or Chuck Norris.
System written by me.
Every Team can collect max. 4 bonuses of 8.

------------------------------------------------------------------

How the System works:

When you start at Spawn you can enter only Stage 1 and 2.
If you finish one of the Stages you have to push a button to gain Points.
Also there is a bar that turns around after you pressed the button where you can enable one of the other 6 Stages for ur team.
You get points for every Stage your Team will finish.

Stage 1 = 1 point
Stage 2 = 2 points
Stage 3 = 3 points
...etc.

That means that you can gain max 36 points in one round.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

When the timer is at the end before your team finished you get a weapon depending on how many points you gained.

For example:

9 points = tmp
22 points = p90
26 points = scout

--------------------------------------------------------------------

Special thanks to Exither. He inspired us with surf_injection to the system of this map.

-=surf_clockwork=- This is one of my oldest projects that I finished. Actually it's a map I made in the days I was less experienced. However I restarted this map for 90% and I decided to fully release it. The map system The players start in the spawn and as they walk towards the first ramp a pre-timer will be activated. When this timer runs out (after 2 minutes) the real timer will start. During the pre-timer, every failure will be forgiven and there will be an instant retry. However, after the first 2 minutes, every player will be sent to jail after a fail. More about the jail later. The surf track is a linear track with high difficulty level. As you start surfing you will move through different environments going from black-white to colourfull. Also there are both compact and spacy surf. Just before the final and hardest surf room, there is water. Land in here and walk into the portal and you will go to jail with a weapon. Then you can kill everyone you see. But watch out! (more on the jail later) There are three time-challenges in the map. When you encounter a dead end, then this is no dead end but a time-challenge. You must surf through a black/white circle/corona. After that, doors will open which will allow you to continue surfing. The trick is to think out how to reach this corona and get through a door before it closes again. These events are time-based and you will see a visual clock which displays the time that is left. There is also a special bonus stage which is a collapsed version of my surf stage in surf_Qlimax_Q. There is a 33.33% chance the bonus stage will be enabled during a round. You can check if it is enabled by starting with the surf track and land into the blue water (where you can go to jail with a weapon). When you are teleported, you are lucky. Only 1 player is allowed in the bonus stage during a round and you only have 10 attempts to beat it. If you fail after 10 tries, then you will be teleported back to spawn. When you are not teleported, then either the teleporter is not activated (try again next round) or someone went in before you got there. The Jail Time is your ally, and your enemy on this map. When you get sent to jail you will see a huge clock. Do not touch this clock, you will instantly die. As you may guess, you will have to clock jump. So when you get sent to jail then immediatly try to focus on where the clock is and try to avoid it while landing in the clock chamber. Try to survive as long as possible until you are teleported out. Then you can try again. Players that went to jail with a weapon also have to watch out. They will have to combine survival and PvP skills in order to get kills. Completing the map You can complete the map in two different ways. Beat the regular surf track or beat the bonus stage. When you beat the map in the regular way, you will be sent to a room above the jail. Players will be teleported and you can choose between 3 buttons. Button 1: Gives you a para and you will be able to kill everyone. (Beware, the other players will get knives so also keep an eye on your health) Button 2: Two panels will lower through the ceiling and all the players will be dropped into the clockjumping room. Now YOU have control over the clock. Press the orange button to increase speed and press the green one to decrease. Button 3: It is silent...suddently the whole area starts to shake and a huge sound can be heard. In a matter of seconds...your enemy team is dead and you get the kills. I hope you have fun. If there are any gameplay-killing bugs then please do message me. If it is just a small detail, then nevermind.
Im the origional author, simply message me if you have any comments/concerns, or if you want to edit it. Constructive Criticism welcomed. Have fun!

The map has 30 spawn points (15 for each team).  However, I would guess that more than 16 players would be fairly chaotic.

This is my first map.

Like I said in the last release here on FPSBanana, there are 30 or so spawn points (15 for each team), but i would only recommend having about 16 players due to crowding.

I may have left a few things out of this list.  Especially considering that I never released Beta2 here on fpsbanana.  So there are some changes that were made between v1o2b and Beta2 that won't be listed here.  But I really hope you guys enjoy my map.  I love knowing that I have contributed to the fun times of the CS surfing community.  <3!

Surf_Ch33s3r_Beta3 Release Notes
--------------------------------
Added push trigger to bottom of hole in pyramid to prevent camping

Added a few teleport labels

Fixed problem where you could take damage from the "O" (If you don't know what this means, ignore it ;))

Fixed CT and T spawn portal mismatch

Fixed jail triggers next to main ramp so they don't tele you to jail just from getting close to the edge

Fixed problem where you could see feet/shadows of players inside the secret room (hopefully)

Fixed an exploit that provided a much easier route to the secret room

Changed kill triggers to jail triggers

Changed water textures (other than jail water) to look translucent instead of looking black

Changed jail so that prisoners cannot see players on top of the secret area

Changed the exterior jail wall facing the "top" to allow all types of ammunition to penetrate

Changed jail doors

This map, surf_castle2 is the sequel to my first surf map ever, surf_castle. It is a medium sized combat map. Your starting weapons are knifes, deagles, and shottys. There is an awp on top of the tower and there are hidden paras in the sewer things. There is a bomb site and a bomb in the tower so if you want you can plant two bombs. The map is HDR and the skybox is custom. I just thought this map deserved better than the first one. The game play goes as follows, you get shot out of the spawn with pushes and then you surf on this oval ramp with arrows that make you go faster. There is a ramp going down the middle of the map also. Enjoy!
